MACRO 19
VARIABLE FIREPOTS
VARIABLE ITSADRAKIN
;This number (30) will give a minimum of 1 1/2 minutes and a max of 15  minutes
;course, the mean is more likely to be about 5
IFVAR FIREPOTS > 25
  RANDOM DUMMY2 1 9 0
  ADD DUMMY2 200
  RANDOM DUMMY3 1 100 0
  AFFECT DUMMY2
  IFVAR DUMMY3 < 20
    DAMAGEALL BURN 25 WHOOSH! Firepots explode around you! You are hit by flying debris!
    RANDOM DUMMY1 1 10 0
    EQUAL FIREPOTS DUMMY1
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 > 21
    IFVAR DUMMY3 < 50
      DAMAGEALL SLASH 16 A firepot explodes nearby. You are hit by flying debris!
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 > 95
    DAMAGEALL BURN 30 A firepot scores a direct hit!
    DAMAGEALL SLASH 60 It explodes, sending shrapnel flying!
    DAMAGEALL BURN 100 Your clothing catches fire, immolating you!
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 > 49
    IFVAR DUMMY3 < 95
      DAMAGEALL CRUSH 50 Heavy stones tumble around you!
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITSADRAKIN = 9
  AFFECT 201
  IFVAR PLRSINROOM ! 0
  DAMAGEALL SLASH 5 You are struck by a falling arrow!
ENDIF
NUMBER 1027
NAME Foyer
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Sparse furnishings decorate this room with occasional tables and chairs
used more for decoration than practical use. To the north one can hear
running water and see the world renowned drakin garden. A highly polished
brass plaque has been embedded into the center of floor here. A spiral
stairway leads to the roof.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 1028
EXIT O 523
ITEM 0 91 ADJ1=355
ITEM 1 86 ADJ1=355
ITEM 2 400 ADJ1=241 ADJ2=32
ITEM 3 1416
ITEM 4 81 VAL2=673
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
Though this plaque has been trod over countless times, it somehow manages
to retain a high degree of lustre, as if it had just been recently placed
here. Delicate lettering, in both the Drakin and Human language flows across
the plaque.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 2
                 "THE ORDER OF THE WAY"
              "Like the points of a star,"
             "good and evil, light and dark,"
           "are diametrically opposing forces."
        "Yet, one would not exist without the other."
         "There exists the middle, where all meet."
            "In the middle there is Harmony,"
              "In the middle is the Way."
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1028
NAME Central Courtyard
ASTRAL
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This courtyard has seen better days. The constant bombardment has crushed
the garden that once grew here.  A small pool to one side is now muddy 
and filled with rocks. The hshed cries of merchants and shopppers can be
heard coming from the shopping arcade to the west, while a long street to
the east contains the housing for the inhabitants of this mighty fortress.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 1030
EXIT SE 1032
EXIT W 1066
EXIT E 2240
EXIT S 1027
EXIT SW 1033
EXIT NW 1031
ITEM 0 1695 ADJ1=1154
ITEM 1 324 ADJ1=294
EXTEND 1 of water
ITEM 2 1062 VAL2=1029
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The torn tarokka bushes hold a few remaining leaves. No blossums are visible.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
The muddy water looks oily.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB RECALL -1
  IFVAR SKILL32 => 1
   IFVAR RAC = 6
    ECHO PLAYER Legend has it that the Tarokka bush, or Ancestor Bush, is imbued with the spirits of ones ancestors. During each blooming of the blossoms the ancestors approval for the past years deeds can be observed. Yellow streaks on crimson means approval, black streaks mean disapproval.
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The creaking of the inner structures of the castle make you nervous.
  ECHO OTHERS %N closes %h eyes and seems to withdraw within %iself for a moment.
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER Your nostrils search through the myriad smells, you miss the flowers. 
  ECHO OTHERS %N lifts %h head to the breeze and draws a deep breath, sighing.
ENDIF
IFVERB GO 2
 DISBAND
  ECHO PLAYER You slowly wade into the muddy water.
  ECHO OTHERS %N slowly wades into the muddy water.
  AFFECT 1029
  ECHO OTHERS %N wades into the water, moving slowly towards you.
  AFFECT 1028
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1029
NAME Refreshing Pool
ASTRAL
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
You feel sad that the water here has been spoiled.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 1028
IFPREVERB DOWN -1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR ORG = 20
    ECHO PLAYER You move to the center of the pool and dive down..
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER ..you follow the path you were taught through a small cave system..
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER ..the cave opens up and you swim to the surface...
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER ..you swim the river until you reach the beach at the inner sea.
    MOVE 530
    SHOWROOM 530
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You move to the center of the pool and dive down..
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER You find yourself swimming through a cave system....
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER ..you realize you may get lost and swim back to the pool.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1030
NAME Forge
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
FORGE
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The temperature difference of this room is dramatically discernible as you
feel the heat from the forge. Tools adorn the wall and the area looks much
like the smithy yard that you have seen in Fayd. Large bellows sit next to
the forge, ready to bring the fire roaring to life, while a pile of logs
sits against the far wall, placed so as not to catch any stray cinders.
Some scrabbled writing across the bin informs you that you can buy steel
here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT SW 1028
ITEM 0 1517
ITEM 1 420
ITEM 2 1416
ITEM 3 1518
ITEM 4 196
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Interspersed amongst the various tools of the smith are beautiful Drakin
weapons that epitomize the highest achievement of blacksmithing. They
have been placed there as a motivation for the smith who always seeks to
outdo himself.
*DESCRIPTION_END
STOREITEM 1372 -1 500
IFPREVERB PUSH 3
  CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You pump the bellows, sending a blast of air over the burning coals in the forge, causing them to glow with an intense, fiery red heat.
    ECHO OTHERS %N pumps the bellows, sending a blast of air over the burning coals in the forge, causing them to glow with an intense, fiery red heat.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH 4
   CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You pick out a suitable piece of wood and heft it into the gaping maw of the forge, causing flames to lick out towards you as the fire roars to life.
    ECHO OTHERS %N picks out a suitable piece of wood and hefts it into the gaping maw of the forge, causing flames to lick out towards you as the fire roars to life.
ENDIF
;
