NUMBER 1032
NAME Church
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This room is unlike any church you have ever seen. Although there is an
altar, it lacks visible signs of statues or holy symbols that you would
commonly find in other churches. Rather the walls are adorned with
what appears to be the family lineages of different Drakin Clans. Heavy
smells of incense fill the room, which seems to have been designed more
for meditation than prayer.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NW 1028
ITEM 0 236
IFVERB PRAY -1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR RAC = 6
   ECHO PLAYER You sit down, close your eyes and open your being to the soothing peace of your ancestors.
   ECHO OTHERS %N sits down and closes %h eyes, chanting a soft mantra to %h ancestors.
   POSITION SIT
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1033
NAME Conference Room
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A huge conference table, made from deeplander stone, adorns the center of
this room, surrounded by equally impressive chairs. Inlaid in gold, on the
center of the table, is a massive serpentine dragon, twisted in the shape
of an eight that appears to be biting its own tail. This chamber is
obviously the meeting place of for the Guildmaster and the Elder brothers.
A large mosaic covers the southern wall, adding a pleasing effect to the
serenity of the room.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 1028
ITEM 0 91 ADJ1=312
ITEM 1 86 ADJ1=312
ITEM 2 547
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
The mosaic is a beautifully done portrayal of, "The Meeting at Ha'Kra."
The meeting, in the year 341, where the spiritual and philosophical leaders
of the Drakin nation gathered to ratify the Code. The meeting took place
after the bloody civil war which almost shattered the Drakin nation.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1066
NAME Shopping Arcade
ASTRAL
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This busy street is a sharp contrast to the other more serene sections of
the castle. Merchants and shoppers hustle by, intent on their business
within the various buildings contained along the narrow road. A large
building to the north, with lettering above the arch spelling out,
"Gem Market", catches your eye.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 1028
EXIT W 1068
ITEM 0 60 VAL2=1067
