NUMBER 1504
NAME Gulbane's Room
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_Start
You enter into Gulbane's room which is like no place else in the castle.
Thick green mist belches forth from a cauldron in a corner. You don't
know if this is a new recipe or a potion experiment, but it smells
strongly of limes. The mist totally obscures the floor and on of the
walls. Another wall consists of stone carvings of the faces of imps,
demons and other fierce beasts. The eyes of the carvings all glow
orange-red and illuminate the room. A desk rises up out of the mist, and
is covered with scrolls. There is a bed here as well, but its normal
appearance sets it apart from the rest of the room.
*DESCRIPTION_END
item 0 1230 adj1=443 adj2=87 adj3=152 val2=1501
item 1 201
item 2 84
;
NUMBER 1505
NAME Prophet's Room
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The complete emptiness of Prophet's room takes you by surprise. In
fact, his entire house is devoid of any furniture or decorations, even
the walls are a blank white. In the very center of the room, however,
there seems to be a magical gate that floats in the air. Gazing into
the gate you can see the landscape of what appears to be another place
or time. The gate seems to almost be alive, and the smells and sounds
of the visions you see appear to be all too real. You quickly surmise
that this must be some sort of space and time field.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 1501
ITEM 0 68 VAL1=5000
IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER The forces of light and darkness swirl together blocking you path.
    ECHO OTHERS The forces of light and darkness swirl together, blocking %N's attempt at entering the portal.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB OPEN 0
  CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The magical portal is not openable.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB UNLOCK 0
  CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The portal is magical and thus has no need for a lock.
ENDIF
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The gate seems to be an ever changing picture surrounded in an ancient
frame of ornate design. The frame itself seems to be made of handcrafted
Urimar and its size is large enough to allow two people to walk through.
Most of the carvings on the frame seem to be in old world Drakin tongue,
yet the language seems to be mixed in with another form of scripting.
 or an instant you think you know where you have seen these symbols before,
but suddenly your mind goes blank and the harder you concentrate the more
difficult it becomes for you to maintain your focus.
*DESCRIPTION_END
