NUMBER 673
NAME Castle, Roof
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
ASTRAL
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
You stand atop the castle, from this vantage you can see Fayd to the north,
the inner sea to the south, and all the surrounding siege works. True to the
word of the dragons the outer walls seems to be unscratched by the bombardment.
However looking down into the courtyard you see that the inner structure is not
so blessed. The wind is stronger up here. Sitting at the floors edge is a large
black cauldron, filled with boiling oil. Standing on both sides of the cauldron
are drakin, ready to refill it. An arch leads into the hanger of the
"Thunderchild." 
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT ABOVE 2168
ITEM 0 81 VAL2=1027
ITEM 1 1169
ITEM 2 60 ADJ1=292 VAL2=1509
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You look down to the front of the castle.
  SHOWROOM 523
ENDIF

