EXIT S 1513
*DESCRIPTION_START
The spacious hold is stacked with orderly rows of crates and barrels
holding provisions for several weeks at the very least. Off to one side
are several stacks of wooden boxes marked with the names of various
members of the Order. To the south, a narrow corridor leads to the
crew's quarters, and a door is set into the northern wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 200 VAL2=1514
;
NUMBER 1513
NAME Thunderchild, Belowdecks
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
EXIT N 1512
*DESCRIPTION_START
A narrow, dimly lit corridor divides the ship in two. At regular
intervals along both sides of the hall are openings closed by sliding
screens that offer at least a modicum of privacy for the higher ranking
members of the crew. A narrow flight of stairs leads back up to the
deck, and the light brightens considerably to the north.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 81 VAL2=1511
;
NUMBER 1514
NAME Thunderchild, War Room
INDOOR_FLOOR
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
Carefully drawn maps and charts line every wall, most with markings and
pins representing targets and trade routes. Comfortable chairs are set
around an enormous wood table, and in one corner, in a wooden tub, is a
tarokka bush, uprooted from the courtyard of the Castle and carefully
tended. A door leads out into the cargo hold.
*DESCRIPTION_END
